{"title":"Grant Petersen and Rivendell in the New Yorker","link":"https://theradavist.com/grant-petersen-and-rivendell-in-the-new-yorker/","date":1726582395000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/09/Grant_Rivendell_NewYorker.jpg?fit=1200,1333&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/09/Grant_Rivendell_NewYorker.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/09/Grant_Rivendell_NewYorker.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/09/Grant_Rivendell_NewYorker.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/09/Grant_Rivendell_NewYorker.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>Grant Petersen, the founder of <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/rivendell/\" target=\"_blank\">Rivendell</a> and one of the pioneers of alt-cycling, has an amazing write-up in the New Yorker about his modus operandi and motivations for encouraging people to ride slowly. We’re big fans of <a href=\"https://rivbike.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Rivendell</a> over here, as we know many of you are. It’s a fantastic read, so roll (slowly) on over to the <a href=\"https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2024/09/23/the-art-of-taking-it-slow\" target=\"_blank\">New Yorker</a> to check it out.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/grant-petersen-and-rivendell-in-the-new-yorker/\">Grant Petersen and Rivendell in the New Yorker</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"0d207bf11329ac1e4394b4fd3da190bc185219cc2d4572c7ca0364916aaec315","category":"Cycling"}